The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A 35-year-old homemaker allegedly killed her husband by hitting him on the head with an iron rod at Domjur, Howrah, on Thursday afternoon. Kamala Das surrendered after walking to Domjur police station with her 12-year-old daughter, who witnessed the incident. Police said Kamalas husband Bablu, 50, used to torture her regularly. According to Kamalas statement, Bablu beat her up on Thursday while she was having lunch. She allegedly hit him on the head when he was sleeping. She was remanded in judicial custody for a day.    Oil leak from a petrol pump reservoir into a drain along Netaji Subhas Road in Howrah was detected on Friday morning after a man threw a cigarette stub into the drain, setting it on fire. Firemen reached the spot and tried to plug the leak.    A 45-year-old peon of Jagaddal post office was found dead in a ditch in Kanchrapara, beside Kalyani Expressway, on Friday morning. Police said Ramprasad Das, a resident of Jagaddal, went missing on Thursday evening. Police said he was hit in the head with a blunt object and his neck was slashed.     Cancer patients in the city will not have to pay the basic fare in AC three-tier and sleeper classes for journeys by mail/express trains for treatment and check-up at recognised hospitals from April 20. Eastern Railway officials said the waiver would be offered on tickets purchased on and after April 20. Those escorting a cancer patient will be eligible for a 75 per cent concession.    Advocate Harish Tandon was appointed a judge of Calcutta High Court on Friday. After his appointment, the number of judges in the court is 29 against the sanctioned strength of 58.     Gauri Pati, 60, was found dead near Belur burning ghat on Friday. The Orissa resident was visiting a relative.                                                                                                                                                  
